Program: Outlook
Title: 21/10/2010
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p00bbpl7
Last Broadcast Date: Fri 22 Oct 2010
IGOR SUTYAGIN The Russian who was exchanged for undercover agents in the biggest spy swap since the cold war. Igor was held in some of Russia's harshest prisons for 11 years but still maintains his innocence. He's now in the UK - his family are still in Russia - but he says he can't return because of fears for his safety. AFRICA UNITED From Rwanda to the World Cup, Africa United is a film about the extraordinary journey of a group of street children who set out across Africa to see their football heroes. Matthew Bannister meets the child stars of the movie that's being called Africa's answer to Slumdog Millionaire. VOLCANO PHOTOGRAPHERS Geoff Mackley and Drew Bristow's photo of the inside of a volcano has been described as the most incredible volcano footage ever. The pair tried for years to get the flim. Show less